This paper focuses on developing a contextual dialog system for natural interactions in autonomous vehicles, which involves understanding passenger intents from spoken interactions and car's vision. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of language/text, audio, and video modalities, which suggests that it could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper deals with multimodal in-cabin interactions, which could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
